notes.body_html:
Hello Shakoor,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
​
​With regards to your order #654164717723164672-75053, I see your order is dispatched and it is being delivered by a courier partner. The estimated delivery date is 07th December 2025.

I would like to inform you that the estimated date of delivery depends on the availability of the medicines and the delivery pin code. Also, be informed that PharmEasy will always try to ensure that your order is delivered at the earliest as we completely understand the urgency of the medicine.

Please note that the estimated date of delivery for courier orders will vary based on the delivery location. Your order will be delivered within the estimated delivery date committed at the time of order placement. Your patience and understanding are highly appreciated in the meantime.
​
​You may also track your order from here https://www.shiprocket.in/shipment-tracking/ with the AWB number BSRC0500629735. 
​
For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels in the App or website listed in the 'Need Help' section.

Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Stay Healthy.

Regards,
Manisha

Hello Sahar,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

I tried to reach you earlier today at 2:37 PM on 8237362944, but unfortunately, I was unable to connect with you.

With regard to your order #654191662245347328-86796, please note that a reattempt will be made, and your order will be delivered as per the estimated delivery date committed at the time of order placement. 

Please be informed the estimated delivery date is 6th December 2025.
​
You can also track your order on the link below with the help of the AWB no. 

Link: https://www.shiprocket.in/shipment-tracking/
AWB: 35899335846903 

For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels in the App or website listed in the Need Help section. Alternatively, you can also call us on 8071324888.

Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Stay healthy.

Regards,
Tahera

Hello Madhu,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

With regards to your order #656184371097894912-16727, I see your order is under process, and the medicines are being arranged. The estimated delivery date is 10th December 2025.

I would like to inform you that the estimated date of delivery depends on the availability of the medicines and the delivery pin code. Also, be informed that PharmEasy will always try to ensure that your order is delivered at the earliest as we completely understand the urgency of the medicine.

Also, I noticed the requested medicine,VALENT 40MG STRIP OF 10 TABLETS, is limited in stock. our Partner Retailer is trying to arrange from other distributors as its stock has been exhausted. The expected time to get medicines arranged is 10th December 2025 at 8:30 AM.

Mumbai - 400050.

To,
PharmEasy.

Sir/Ma'am,

On 29/11/2025, I booked two blood tests and one urine test from you. Order
ID: 6210897. My blood and urine sample was taken by your technician who
visited my house to collect the sample.

Within some time of the blood sample collection, I began getting immense
pain in my left arm from which the sample was collected and I am getting
the same pain till today. There is also discoloration of my arm and the
issue is not resolved till today. I have shared a photo of my left arm in
the attachments.

Today, 06/12/2025, a technician visited my house to collect my samples as I
had ordered three blood tests and one urine test. The technique used by him
to collect my blood sample was totally absurd, painful and also wrong due
to which the laboratory has cancelled/rejected my sample. The blood sample
was pulled out from my right arm. He apparently pulled out very little
amount of blood which is quarter of the tube for containing blood and he
pulled the blood out from my upper arm giving me immense pain in my upper
arm due to which I am in constant pain now and cannot fold my arm without
pain. I repeatedly asked him whether the procedure used by him was correct
as never before this procedure was used on me whenever I have done a blood
test to which he replied it was the correct procedure. When I checked my
PharmEasy app, I saw that the samples were rejected and the tests were
cancelled at the laboratory and also that fresh blood samples would have to
be collected from me. I am already in excruciating pain in both my arms due
to the acts of your technicians and I wouldn't want to give my samples to
you again as I don't trust you due to the bad deficient service provided by
you. In the attachments is the screenshot of the SMS received by me and
also proof of the cancellation of my blood tests by the laboratory. I state
that I am in extreme pain in both my arms and having great difficulty to
even type this present e-mail.

I state that gross negligence has been committed by your technicians due to
which I am in extreme physical as well as mental agony and I reserve my
right to take out appropriate legal action against you which includes
approaching the consumer court against you and also reporting you to the
relevant Government authorities for misleading and dangerous practices
endangering lives of people.

I further state that the urine sample given by me was darkish yellow,
however the report states that the sample was pale yellow which further
puts a major question mark on the credibility of the tests done by your
side.

You are therefore called upon through this e-mail to compensate me for the
mental agony and physical harm committed on me and also provide me a refund
for the amount paid by me for the tests failure to which I reserve my right
to approach the Consumer Court against you and also report you to the
Police as well as other Government authorities.

Yours faithfully,
Adv. Adnan Mookhtiar

Dear Sir,
I am surprised that you are offering me lame excuses, glorifying the efforts of your suppliers in their efforts in sending a wrong item.
In the case of other suppliers of medicine items. 
They refund the amount if an item is not available, instead of sending a wrong item. 
They don't argue with a customer and tell him to accept a wrong item.
They take the word of a customer if an item is short supplied and refund the amount paid by the customer. 
I am extremely disappointed by your attitude supporting the supplier. 
Please cancel my entire order and refund the amount paid by me, as I am unhappy with your services. 
Regards,
Ravindra Vaidya 
Pune

Hello Arunabh,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with regards to your order #654095958471843840-18013, we apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.

As per update received from our team, please be informed that we have raised a return request for 01 quantity of theFORMEN DERMA ROLLER FOR HAIR GROWTH | 540 (0.5 MM) TITANIUM MICRO-NEEDLES | GROWTH ACTIVATOR (1 PC)   on 09th December 2025. Please be informed, items being returned should be in their original manufacturer’s packaging with labels and barcode intact.
 
Please note that the medicine will be collected within 48 hours from the day the request is raised. Once the medicine is returned, it will be verified by our partner retailer at the store. The refund will be processed and initiated within 5 business days. Also, once the refund is initiated it would reflect in your original source account within 7-10 business days.
 
We appreciate your patience in the meantime.
 
We are marking the ticket as resolved. If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.
 
For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!
